plot: J.D. Vance's struggle to conform during political campaigns. Exploring the U.S. school lunch program's challenge of providing nutritious meals within budget constraints, highlighting the advantages of Universal Free Meals.

John Oliver talks about J.D. Vance's innate nature of can't being weird on the campaign trail. Also, he discusses the national school lunch program in the United States that how difficult is to balance between nutrition and student's interest to eat them with a limited budget. He points out the benefits of the Universal Free Meals and the real example of it.—Niaz Islam Arif
